A war can be defined as a conflict between two armed parties. It is important to point out that many wars have taken place over the past years. Many countries have developed some deadly weapons that can be used during a war. However, it is very important to point out that there are some weapons that are banned in modern warfare. Let us carefully identify some of these weapons.

1. Incendiary Devices
Incendiary weapons are used to set fire on important things. One incendiary weapon can burn a large portion of land. It should also be said that this weapon can be used to destroy a lot of things. However, incendiary devices are not allowed during warfare. There is a United Nations Treaty that prohibits the use of incendiary weapons.
2. Biological weapons
Biological weapons are usually very dangerous. However, it should be said that biological weapons are not allowed during war. The Biological Weapons Convention is a treaty that prohibits the development of biological weapons.
3. Blinding Laser Weapons
A blinding Laser weapon can be used to cause blindness during war. However, it is important to note the fact that blinding laser weapons are banned during war. The Protocol on Blinding Laser Weapons has been in effect for many years now. This treaty prohibits the use of blinding laser weapons during war. This treaty has been signed by many countries.



